-- Mali, Ghana Advance to Africa Cup of Nations Soccer Semifinals
-- B y   B o b   B e n s c h
-- 2013-02-02T21:42:01Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2013-02-02/mali-ghana-advance-to-africa-cup-of-nations-soccer-semifinals.html
Mali defeated host South Africa 3-1
in a penalty shootout and Ghana beat Cape Verde 2-0 to advance
to the Africa Cup of Nations soccer semifinals.  Mali goalkeeper Soumaila Diakite made two saves in the
shootout and his teammates converted all three of their
attempts. The game in Durban went to penalties after finishing
1-1 after extra time.  In the opening quarterfinal in  Port Elizabeth , Mubarek
Wakaso came off the bench to score twice in the second half to
give Ghana the victory.  Mali play Ivory Coast or Nigeria in one semifinal on Feb.
6, while Ghana meets  Burkina Faso  or Togo. The remaining two
quarterfinal matches will be played tomorrow.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Bob Bensch at 
 bbensch@bloomberg.net  